This paper discusses the effect of phase noise and channel variations on the performance of communication systems, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The study also considers the impact of fading, which is a common phenomenon in electromagnetic (EM) waves, making cs.EM a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of system parameters such as center frequency and bandwidth, which are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and networked systems (cs.NI).
